==English==

===Etymology===
Presumably: [[touchdown]] + [[back]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{fb}} The result of a play (usually a [[kickoff]] or [[punt]]) in which the ball passes out the back of the [[end zone]] or a team otherwise gains possession of the ball in their own end zone.
#:''The ball sailed into the end zone for a touchback and the Eagles had possession on the 20-yard line.'' [http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/gameday/postGameArchive.jsp?id=16746]

